block.description:
Run @run@ once and reify its outcome: its value as `succeeded`, or a caught `throw` / `panic` as `failed`,
folding the two failure channels into one sum. This is the single boundary where a failure is caught — every
provider below composes retries out of it. @run@'s effect is the OVERWRITE row `{...E, throw[Error]}` (not the
union `E | throw[Error]`) precisely because this handler discharges the throw — the discord-provider shape;
@run@'s other effects @E@ flow through unchanged.
